The couplet is in **Diwan-E-Ghalib**, chapter 213. The English translation of the opening verse reads: *"This world is but a children's game, a vast display, / Where night and day a spectacle unfolds my way."* The ghazal's 14 couplets sustain this posture of sovereign detachment — the world, Solomon's throne, Christ's miracles, even Kaaba and Church, all dissolve into spectacle before the poet's gaze.
